ce:section.ce:para:
Encouraged by the excellent polarity sensitivity of LD-CPD, the photostability, ionic strength and selectivity of LD-CPD were further evaluated. When excited with 435 nm for 150 min or stored under natural conditions for 10 days, the LD-CPD exhibits good resistance to photobleaching (Figs. S7A and B), which can be utilized for long-term bioimaging. And excellent resistance to ionic strength was also proved by Fig. S7C. As depicted in Fig. S7D, no significant changes in the fluorescence intensity ratio (I/I

                           0
                        ) were observed in the presence of some potential interferents, including metal ions, amino acids and other small biological molecules, indicating the high selectivity towards polarity. To sum up, LD-CPD has desirable fluorescence properties, making them promising for the application of cellular lipid droplet imaging.
